direct_enhancements.reason: Both methods involve processing form elements and collecting data from them.
The submit method relies on the elements method to gather form data before submission.
Both methods involve selecting elements based on certain criteria, with similar control flow and exception handling.
Both methods manipulate the list of form elements, with addElement adding new elements that elements() might later process.
Both methods handle potential exceptions related to element manipulation and attribute removal.
Both methods involve extracting or manipulating text content from elements, though in different contexts.
Both methods generate HTML content, though elements() focuses on form elements and html() on the entire document.
Both methods involve creating copies of elements, though clone() is more general and elements() is specific to form elements.
Both methods involve creating elements from encoded data, though createFromEncoded is more specific to text nodes.
